column168: AT ABOUT 3:45 P.M., JULY 10, 1984, OUR PEOPLE WERE NOTIFIED BY THE CITY OF FT. WORTH FIRE DEPARTMENT THAT THERE WAS A CAR OF CHLORINE LEAKING AT DIXIE PETRO CHEMICAL, INC., WHICH IS LOCATED NEAR OUR EAST YARD AT FORT WORTH. THIS CAR, ACFX 85287, HAD BEEN SPOTTED AT DIXIE PETRO CHEMICAL ON JULY 1, 1 984, AND WAS IN THE PROCESS OF BEING UNLOADED BY MEANS OF A 4-INCH HOSE CON NECTED TO THE BOTTOM OF CAR INTO DIXIE PETRO CHEMICAL'S TANK.  FT. WORTH FI RE DEPARTMENT AND EMERGENCY RESPONSE TEAM WERE ON THE SCENE.  INVESTIGATION DEVELOPS THAT GATX 50293, TANK CAR ALSO LOADED WITH CHLORINE, SHIPPED BY D IAMOND CHEMICAL CO., HOUSTON, TEXAS, TO DIXIE PETRO CHEMICAL AND SPOTTED ON THEIR TRACK AT ABOUT 10:00 A.M., JULY 10TH, (WITH HAND BRAKES SET, AIR ON CAR, DERAIL AND SKATES ON TRACK), ROLLED DOWN TRACK, TEARING OUT DERAIL AND KNOCKING SKATES OFF TRACK, AND STRUCK AFCX 85287.  IMPACT DERAILED A END E AST END OF ACFX 85287 AND CAUSED UNLOADING HOSE TO BREAK LOOSE, RESULTING I N MINIMAL LEAKAGE FROM UNLOADING HOSE AND T-VALVE; HOWEVER, THERE WAS NO DA MAGE TO EITHER CAR.  FIRE DEPARTMENT ADVISED THAT LEAKING REPORTED AT TOP O F CAR WAS CHLORINE GAS TRAPPED IN THE T-VALVE, WHICH WAS RELEASED, AND THAT AFCX 85287 ITSELF WAS NOT LEAKING EXCEPT FROM BOTTOM HOSE CONNECTION, WHIC H WAS STOPPED AT 4:05 P.M.  APPARENTLY THE DERAIL HAD BEEN TAMPERED WITH BY VANDALS WHICH ALLOWED GATX 50293 TO ROLL DOWN TRACK AND INTO GATX 85287. FRA REPRESENTATIVE BOB WILSON AND HOWARD MANNING OF CHEMTREC WERE NOTIFIED AT 4:30 PM.  SEE ALSO REPORT NUMBER 84070552.
